,('reading', 'According to the passage, where did the ancient Olympic Games originate?', 'The Olympic Games, now a global sporting celebration held every four years, began in ancient Greece. The first recorded Games took place in 776 BCE in the city of Olympia, in honor of the god Zeus. Initially, the competition included only a single footrace. Over time, events like wrestling, chariot racing, and the discus throw were added. Athletes came from city-states across Greece, and a truce was declared during the Games so that competitors could travel safely. The modern Olympics were revived in Athens in 1896, inspired by the ancient tradition, and have since grown to include hundreds of sports and thousands of athletes from every nation.', '["Athens, Greece", "Sparta, Greece", "Olympia, Greece", "Rome, Italy"]'::jsonb, 2, 1, 'The passage directly states: "The first recorded Games took place in 776 BCE in the city of Olympia."')

